tables.description: The action_tracker table represents a record of actions taken in response to incidents. It stores information about the action, the owner responsible, and the status of the action. This table is typically used in analytics and business workflows to track progress and identify areas for improvement in incident management.

columns.description: The action_id column represents a unique identifier for each action recorded in the action_tracker table. It is an integer value that stores a unique action ID. This column is used to track and reference individual actions within the action_tracker table.

The incident_id column represents the ID of the incident to which the action is related. It is an integer value that stores a reference to the incident record in the incidents table. This column is used to link actions to their corresponding incidents.

The action_item column represents a brief description of the action taken in response to an incident. It is a text value that stores a concise summary of the action. This column is used to track the specific actions taken in response to incidents.

columns.description: The owner column represents the employee responsible for taking the action. It is a character varying value that stores the employee's name or ID. This column is used to track accountability and ownership of actions taken in response to incidents.

The due_date column represents the deadline for completing the action. It is a date value that stores the expected completion date. This column is used to track progress and ensure timely completion of actions.

The action_status column represents the current status of the action. It is a character varying value that stores the status (e.g., 'in progress', 'completed', 'deferred'). This column is used to track the progress and status of actions taken in response to incidents.

tables.description: The employees table stores information about the organization's workforce, including employee IDs, full names, departments, job titles, and email addresses. This table is crucial for HR management and is often used to track employee information, departmental structures, and job roles within the organization.

columns.description: The employee_id column represents a unique identifier for each employee in the organization. It is an integer value that stores a unique employee ID. This column is used to track and reference individual employees within the employees table.
The full_name column represents the employee's full name. It is a character varying value that stores the employee's name. This column is used to track employee information and contact details.

The department column represents the employee's department or team. It is a character varying value that stores the department name. This column is used to track departmental structures and employee assignments.

The job_title column represents the employee's job title or role. It is a character varying value that stores the job title. This column is used to track job roles and responsibilities within the organization.
The email column represents the employee's email address. It is a character varying value that stores the email address. This column is used to track employee contact information.

tables.description: The incidents table represents a record of all incidents that have occurred within the organization. It stores information about the incident date, category, location, severity, and description, as well as the employee who reported the incident. This table is used in analytics and business workflows to identify trends, track incident rates, and inform risk management strategies.

columns.description: The incident_id column represents a unique identifier for each incident recorded in the incidents table. It is an integer value that stores a unique incident ID. This column is used to track and reference individual incidents within the incidents table.
The incident_date column represents the date on which the incident occurred. It is a date value that stores the incident date. This column is used to track incident dates and identify trends.

The incident_category column represents the category or type of incident. It is a character varying value that stores the incident category. This column is used to track incident types and identify patterns.

The site_location column represents the location where the incident occurred. It is a character varying value that stores the site location. This column is used to track incident locations and identify trends.

The severity column represents the severity level of the incident. It is a character varying value that stores the severity level (e.g., 'low', 'medium', 'high'). This column is used to track incident severity and identify areas for improvement.

The description column represents a detailed description of the incident. It is a text value that stores a concise summary of the incident. This column is used to track incident details and identify root causes.

columns.description: The reported_by column represents the employee who reported the incident. It is an integer value that stores the employee ID. This column is used to track incident reporting and identify areas for improvement.

tables.description: The risk_register table stores information about potential hazards and risks within the organization. It includes details about the hazard type, description, assessment date, and risk rating. This table is used to identify and prioritize risks, inform mitigation strategies, and ensure compliance with regulatory requirements.

columns.description: The risk_id column represents a unique identifier for each risk recorded in the risk_register table. It is an integer value that stores a unique risk ID. This column is used to track and reference individual risks within the risk_register table.

The assessment_date column represents the date on which the risk was assessed. It is a date value that stores the assessment date. This column is used to track risk assessment dates and identify trends.
The hazard_type column represents the type of hazard or risk. It is a character varying value that stores the hazard type. This column is used to track risk types and identify patterns.

The hazard_description column represents a detailed description of the hazard or risk. It is a text value that stores a concise summary of the hazard. This column is used to track risk details and identify root causes.

columns.description: The risk_rating column represents the risk rating or severity level. It is an integer value that stores the risk rating. This column is used to track risk severity and identify areas for improvement.

tables.description: The trainings table represents a record of employee training and development activities. It stores information about the training title, employee ID, completion date, and status. This table is used in analytics and business workflows to track employee training records, identify training needs, and inform talent development strategies.

columns.description: The training_id column represents a unique identifier for each training recorded in the trainings table. It is an integer value that stores a unique training ID. This column is used to track and reference individual trainings within the trainings table.

The employee_id column represents the ID of the employee who participated in the training. It is an integer value that stores the employee ID. This column is used to track employee training records and identify training needs.

The training_title column represents the title of the training program. It is a character varying value that stores the training title. This column is used to track training programs and identify areas for improvement.

The completion_date column represents the date on which the training was completed. It is a date value that stores the completion date. This column is used to track training completion dates and identify trends.

The status column represents the current status of the training. It is a character varying value that stores the status (e.g., 'in progress', 'completed', 'deferred'). This column is used to track training progress and identify areas for improvement.
